<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1109,1530]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,784,1145,1170]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Diagnostic description (female, male unknown).</emphasis>
General characteristics as for the genus. Squamipterous, tegmina shorter than pronotum, not overlapping, approximately circular in shape (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1144,1182,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,206,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1328]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic characters of Aprosphylini: A. G. duplessisae, female, dorsal view; B. G. c a p e n s i s, ditto; C. G. p e d e s - tris, female head and pronotum, lateral view; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. ditto, fastigium of vertex; F. Aprosphylus olszanowskii, fastigium of vertex; G. G. pedestris, female subgenital plate; H. G. longipes, ditto; I. G. duplessisae, ditto; J. G. c a p e n s i s, ditto; K. G. longipes, male cerci and subgenital plate; L. G. duplessisae, ditto; M. G. capensis, ditto." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209713/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Figs. 
<number box="[1131,1144,1182,1206]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D); hind wing vestigial but still present. Fore and mid femora with 
<number box="[653,695,1218,1242]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
anterior ventral margin only; hind femur with 
<number box="[1235,1276,1218,1242]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
teeth on both ventral margins. Subgenital plate with widely angular incision (
<figureCitation box="[863,929,1254,1278]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,206,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1328]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diagnostic characters of Aprosphylini: A. G. duplessisae, female, dorsal view; B. G. c a p e n s i s, ditto; C. G. p e d e s - tris, female head and pronotum, lateral view; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. ditto, fastigium of vertex; F. Aprosphylus olszanowskii, fastigium of vertex; G. G. pedestris, female subgenital plate; H. G. longipes, ditto; I. G. duplessisae, ditto; J. G. c a p e n s i s, ditto; K. G. longipes, male cerci and subgenital plate; L. G. duplessisae, ditto; M. G. capensis, ditto." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209713/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[915,929,1254,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
G); ratio ovipositor/hind femur 
<number box="[1283,1395,1254,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="0.585" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.60</number>
</paragraph>
